Your words, calm and logical, cut through his panic. He sees the truth in them, the sincerity in your gaze. The wild fear in his eyes recedes, replaced by a flicker of determined hope. He nods slowly, his shoulders slumping in a mixture of relief and resignation. "You're right," he murmurs. "Of course, you're right. Anything for Lily."

With a trembling hand, Bram fumbles with a small, worn leather pouch tied to his belt. He loosens the drawstring and carefully counts out twenty gold coins, their metallic gleam faint in the firelight. He pushes them across the table to you. "It's all I can spare for now. The rest is yours when she's safe." He then unhooks a torch from his belt, its end blackened with soot. "I... I also have this. It's not much, but it may help in the dark."

A wave of profound relief washes over the farmer's face, as if a great weight has been lifted. "Thank you," he says, his voice thick with emotion. "Gods, thank you. Please... bring my girl home." He gives you a final, pleading look before retreating to a quiet corner of the tavern, his anxious vigil beginning. The choice is now yours. You can explore the village for supplies or perhaps allies by going 'outside', or you can begin the journey to Darkhollow Cave by heading east.

